/ evaluator): `get_session(request)` runs before `csrf_ok`, so an unauthenticated POST redirects to `/signin` (303) and an authenticated POST with a missing/wrong CSRF token returns 403. The `make_app` factory gains an `@app.exception_handler(eden_storage.errors.NotFound)` that translates raised storage/wire `NotFound` into the same `_error.html` 404 page the existing HTTP-404 handler renders (the prior handler only caught HTTP 404 *responses*, not raised `NotFound` exceptions). [`routes/admin.py`](reference/services/web-ui/src/eden_web_ui/routes/admin.py) is mounted unconditionally; the work-refs sub-page handles the `repo=None` case in-template. Tests cover per-route validation (`test_admin_routes.py`, 33 tests), cross-request flows including planner-claim → admin-reclaim round trip + admin trial-detail rendering for an evaluator-seeded trial (`test_admin_flow.py`, 3 tests), security invariants including unauthenticated-POST-redirects-before-CSRF, error/reclaimed banner allowlist, ref-name regex rejection of every traversal/escape variant including `refs/heads/trial/*` / `HEAD` / shell-injection-shaped names with `subprocess.run` asserted uncalled, server-side `expected_old_sha` source (the form-hidden field is overridden by the live SHA), and the `javascript:` URI scheme allowlist on trial detail (`test_admin_security.py`, 21 tests), partial-write recovery for the four failure modes — `IllegalTransition` on terminal reclaim, transport-shaped `Exception` from the store with no auto-retry, GET-time/POST-time eligibility divergence, and CAS-miss → `?error=ref-changed` (`test_admin_partial_write.py`, 5 tests), and a `pytest.mark.e2e` real-subprocess test that drives planner-claim + admin-reclaim through real HTTP and verifies the resulting `task.reclaimed` event with `cause=operator` via a separate `StoreClient` (`test_admin_e2e.py`).
